Relationships.Enemies & Allies:
Orcus was one third of the triad of demon lords―including Graz'zt and Demogorgon―that engaged in ongoing war with one another.While ''[[Champions of Ruin]]'' state [[Eltab]] was among the three demon lords in constant battle with one another, nearly every other source includes Demogorgon among the trio. He viewed Graz'zt as a self-aggrandized narcissist, Their conflict predated the [[Days of Thunder]] if not the formation of [[Toril]] itself.{{Speculation}}

The Prince of the Undead developed strong enmity with the [[Raven Queen]], the goddess of death that dwelled within the [[Shadowfell]].{{Cite dragon/397/Faith & Heresy|4}} At one point, Orcus and his minions carried out a series of schemes in an ongoing effort to strip her of her divine powers.

For a brief time, he forged a tenuous alliance with [[Yeenoghu]] the Lord of Savagery, and [[Iggwilv]], the mortal daughter of [[Baba Yaga]]. Orcus and Iggwilv became involved in an elaborate scheme to overthrow Demogorgon as Prince of Demons.{{Cite dungeon/150/Prince of Demons|62}}

Orcus was a patron of sorts to the [[Oerth]]ian mage [[Vecna]], and was said to have offered him the ritual by which he which he became the first lich. He was even pleased with the work of Vecna's one-time follower [[Acererak]], who traveled the planes in search of new and horrific ways to slay innocents.{{Cite adventurers league/Streams of Crimson|44}} Acererak even turned to the worship of Orcus for a time.

Worshipers.Regions:
Orcus had cults dedicated to his worship all across [[Faerûn]], including the realms of [[Vaasa]] and [[Damara]]. In the [[Bloodstone Lands]], Orcus' worship was coordinated by the [[Cult of the Goat's Head]], and in the [[Neverwinter Wood]], by the [[Hunt Lords]]. Despite its transformation into a realm of undeath, Orcus viewed [[Thay]] under the [[Szass Tam]] as a mere petty fiefdom.{{Cite adventurers league/Streams of Crimson|44}}

Temples of Orcus could be found throughout the many planes of existence,

His influence was not limited to the Abyss and the Prime Material Plane. Many of Orcus' dark servants spread out across the [[Shadowfell]], determined to commit horrific deeds in his name. In the Shadowfell, Orcus' cultists took over the dark settlements of [[Moil]], and [[Evernight]], the dark echo of [[Neverwinter]] in Faerûn. Several Shadowfell cults even banded together for a time to raise up Orcus as a new God of Death, to take the place of the [[Raven Queen]], going so far as to scour the [[Plane of Dreams]] for clues to their quest.
